						               													<description>In the small backwoods town of Jethro, Texas on April 3rd, 1989, Buddy Edmunds&amp;mdash;owner of Big Daddy&amp;rsquo;s Used Car Lot&amp;mdash;was brutally murdered in his own living room.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Candy Edmunds, his bride of only three months, was wrongly convicted of his murder and spent the past 30 years of her life behind bars for a crime she didn&amp;rsquo;t commit.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Your job is to get Candy released from prison and figure out who really killed Buddy. Do you have what it takes to crack this unsolved case file?&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In order to solve this cold case murder mystery game you&amp;rsquo;ll need to find 3 separate clues that crack open the case. First prove why the convicted woman must be innocent. Then disprove a key suspect's alibi and finally identify the clue that will close this case for good. With 3 different mysteries to solve in order to play the game, this case will challenge your investigative abilities.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;To get past each step of the case you&amp;rsquo;ll need to visit an online answer page that requires you to prove you cracked it. If you don&amp;rsquo;t have the answer right you can keep investigating without being spoiled by the right answers.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
